Description: Builds an offline, AI-native reasoning layer on top of the
    'ksTFL' clinical tables framework. Reads the metadata and data JSON
    artefacts produced by 'ksTFL' save_report(), compiles them into a
    self-contained study registry of table contexts, and provides an
    'ellmer'-backed chat with registered tools so a medical writer can ask
    questions across the whole set of study statistical results and draft
    clinical study report (CSR) narratives. Works with local models via
    Ollama or LM Studio, or hosted OpenAI-compatible providers.
